  "text": "There are some downstream genes transactivated by NKX2.5, and mutations in several target genes have been linked to AF, including the genes encoding ANF and gap junction protein connexin40 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Therefore, it is probable that mutated NKX2.5 confers susceptibility to AF by decreasing expressions of target genes.",
